Package: SICNN
Title: Smooth Information Criterion Neural Networks Using 'torch'
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Aliaksandr", "Hubin", email = "aliaksandr.hubin@nmbu.no", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Andrew", "McInerney", email = "andrew.mcinerney@ul.ie", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Smooth Information Criterion Neural Networks (SICNNs) are implemented 
    using 'torch', an R interface to the LibTorch backend. Developed as an 
    evolution of Latent Binary Bayesian Neural Networks (LBBNNs) described 
    in Hubin and Storvik (2024) <doi:10.3390/math12060788> and implemented 
    in the 'LBBNN' R package <https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=LBBNN>, 
    SICNNs provide a 
    scalable and continuous approach to parameter pruning by leveraging a smooth 
    approximation of the L0 norm (SIC), as described in O'Neill and Burke (2023) 
    <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2212.12644>. The architecture supports deep structures 
    with input-skip connections to facilitate feature selection in high-dimensional 
    settings.
